Juventus beat Monaco 1-0 in Champions League quarter-final first leg on Tuesday night . 
  Juventus side had an average age of 30 years and 64 days against Monaco . 
  Gianluigi Buffon (37) and Andrea Pirlo (35) started the match . 
  Inter Milan fielded the oldest starting line-up in the Champions League back in February 2012 . 
  Portsmouth fielded the second oldest side in the Premier League . 
  Arturo Vidal scored the only goal of the game for Juventus . 
 